/*
:name: condout_const_arms
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: condout_const_arms.condout
:pyrope_top: condout_const_arms.condout
*/

// Regression (constprop miscompile, repro A): BOTH if-arm writes to an io
// OUTPUT are comptime constants. Each arm's store used to be absorbed into
// the symbol table and dropped (the arm value "is known"), leaving the
// output undriven — cgen emitted an all-unknown poison const instead of a
// mux. Output stores are now always kept (classify_statement_impl's
// io-output guard), so tolg's lower_if merges both arms into a real mux.
//
// NOTE: the then/else constant ORDER is deliberate (1 then 2): tolg's
// lower_if currently sizes the merged mux from the var's LAST recorded
// write (upass_tolg mw_lookup), a separate pre-existing width bug. With the
// wider constant in the else arm the mux is sized correctly either way.
comb condout(s:bool) -> (o:u2) {
  if s {
    o = 1
  } else {
    o = 2
  }
}
